## Memory Profiling

```csharp
public class MemoryProfiler
{
    public static MemorySnapshot TakeSnapshot(string label)
    {
        GC.Collect();
        GC.WaitForPendingFinalizers();
        GC.Collect();

        return new MemorySnapshot
        {
            Label = label,
            Timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow,
            TotalMemory = GC.GetTotalMemory(false),
            Gen0Collections = GC.CollectionCount(0),
            Gen1Collections = GC.CollectionCount(1),
            Gen2Collections = GC.CollectionCount(2)
        };
    }

    public static void CompareSnapshots(MemorySnapshot before, MemorySnapshot after)
    {
        var memoryDiff = after.TotalMemory - before.TotalMemory;
        var gen0Diff = after.Gen0Collections - before.Gen0Collections;
        var gen1Diff = after.Gen1Collections - before.Gen1Collections;
        var gen2Diff = after.Gen2Collections - before.Gen2Collections;

        Console.WriteLine("\n=== Memory Profile Comparison ===");
        Console.WriteLine($"Before: {before.Label} at {before.Timestamp}");
        Console.WriteLine($"After:  {after.Label} at {after.Timestamp}");
        Console.WriteLine($"Memory Delta: {memoryDiff / 1024.0:F2} KB");
        Console.WriteLine($"GC Gen0: {gen0Diff}, Gen1: {gen1Diff}, Gen2: {gen2Diff}");

        if (memoryDiff > 1024 * 1024) // > 1 MB
        {
            Console.WriteLine("⚠️ WARNING: Significant memory increase detected!");
        }
    }
}

public class MemorySnapshot
{
    public string Label { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime Timestamp { get; set; }
    public long TotalMemory { get; set; }
    public int Gen0Collections { get; set; }
    public int Gen1Collections { get; set; }
    public int Gen2Collections { get; set; }
}
```

## Best Practices Checklist

### Rendering Optimization

- ✅ **Use dirty region tracking** for all custom views
- ✅ **Cache static content** (backgrounds, icons, formatted text)
- ✅ **Implement render layers** for complex UIs
- ✅ **Clip drawing operations** to visible regions
- ✅ **Batch draw calls** when possible
- ✅ **Use GPU rendering** for complex graphics
- ✅ **Profile frame times** and target 60 FPS (16.67ms per frame)

### Memory Management

- ✅ **Use SafeHandle** for all native resources
- ✅ **Implement IDisposable** on classes holding unmanaged resources
- ✅ **Free P/Invoke allocations** immediately after use
- ✅ **Pool frequently allocated objects**
- ✅ **Avoid string allocations** in hot paths
- ✅ **Monitor GC collections** and minimize Gen2 collections
- ✅ **Use weak references** for caches

### Layout Optimization

- ✅ **Minimize layout passes** by caching measurements
- ✅ **Use absolute layout** for static positioning
- ✅ **Avoid nested layouts** when possible
- ✅ **Virtualize long lists** with CollectionView
- ✅ **Defer offscreen layout** until needed

### Text and Fonts

- ✅ **Cache shaped text** (SKTextBlob)
- ✅ **Limit font variations** to reduce shaping overhead
- ✅ **Use system fonts** when possible
- ✅ **Preload fonts** at startup
- ✅ **Measure text once** and cache results

### Images

- ✅ **Decode images asynchronously** off the UI thread
- ✅ **Implement multi-level caching** (memory + disk)
- ✅ **Resize images** to display size
- ✅ **Use appropriate formats** (PNG for UI, JPEG for photos)
- ✅ **Lazy load images** in lists

## Continuous Performance Monitoring

```csharp
public class PerformanceMonitor
{
    private static readonly PerformanceMonitor _instance = new();
    public static PerformanceMonitor Instance => _instance;

    private readonly ConcurrentQueue<PerformanceEvent> _events = new();
    private Timer? _reportTimer;

    public void Start()
    {
        _reportTimer = new Timer(_ => GenerateReport(), null, TimeSpan.FromMinutes(1), TimeSpan.FromMinutes(1));
    }

    public void RecordEvent(string category, string operation, double milliseconds)
    {
        _events.Enqueue(new PerformanceEvent
        {
            Category = category,
            Operation = operation,
            Milliseconds = milliseconds,
            Timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow
        });

        // Keep last 10,000 events
        while (_events.Count > 10000)
        {
            _events.TryDequeue(out _);
        }
    }

    private void GenerateReport()
    {
        var events = _events.ToArray();
        var slowEvents = events.Where(e => e.Milliseconds > 16.67).ToArray();

        if (slowEvents.Length > 0)
        {
            Console.WriteLine($"\n⚠️ {slowEvents.Length} slow operations detected in last minute:");

            foreach (var evt in slowEvents.Take(10))
            {
                Console.WriteLine($"  {evt.Category}/{evt.Operation}: {evt.Milliseconds:F2}ms");
            }
        }
    }
}

public class PerformanceEvent
{
    public string Category { get; set; } = "";
    public string Operation { get; set; } = "";
