Caching rendered content is one of the most effective optimization techniques available. OpenMaui's Skia-based rendering system provides multiple caching strategies to eliminate redundant drawing operations.

## Understanding Render Caching

Every time a view is drawn, SkiaSharp executes a series of drawing commands—filling rectangles, stroking paths, rendering text with font shaping. For static or infrequently changing content, this work is wasteful. Render caching stores the output of these operations in an `SKBitmap` or `SKImage` that can be quickly blitted to the canvas.

## Implementing View-Level Caching

The `SkiaView` base class supports render caching through a simple pattern:

```csharp
public class CachedSkiaView : SkiaView
{
    private SKBitmap? _renderCache;
    private bool _cacheInvalidated = true;

    protected override void OnPropertyChanged(string propertyName = null)
    {
        base.OnPropertyChanged(propertyName);

        // Invalidate cache when visual properties change
        if (propertyName == nameof(BackgroundColor) ||
            propertyName == nameof(Width) ||
            propertyName == nameof(Height))
        {
            InvalidateCache();
        }
    }

    public void InvalidateCache()
    {
        _cacheInvalidated = true;
        InvalidateSurface();
    }

    protected override void OnDraw(SKCanvas canvas, int width, int height)
    {
        if (_cacheInvalidated || _renderCache == null)
        {
            // Recreate cache
            _renderCache?.Dispose();
            _renderCache = new SKBitmap(width, height);

            using var cacheCanvas = new SKCanvas(_renderCache);
            DrawContent(cacheCanvas, width, height);

            _cacheInvalidated = false;
        }

        // Fast blit from cache
        canvas.DrawBitmap(_renderCache, 0, 0);
    }

    protected virtual void DrawContent(SKCanvas canvas, int width, int height)
    {
        // Expensive drawing operations here
    }

    protected override void Dispose(bool disposing)
    {
        if (disposing)
        {
            _renderCache?.Dispose();
        }
        base.Dispose(disposing);
    }
}
```

## Text Render Caching

Text rendering with HarfBuzz shaping is particularly expensive for complex scripts (Arabic, Devanagari, CJK). The `SkiaLabel` implementation benefits significantly from text caching:

```csharp
public class TextRenderCache
{
    private readonly Dictionary<TextCacheKey, SKTextBlob> _cache = new();
    private const int MaxCacheSize = 1000;

    private record TextCacheKey(
        string Text,
        string FontFamily,
        float FontSize,
        SKFontStyleWeight Weight,
        SKFontStyleSlant Slant
    );

    public SKTextBlob GetOrCreateTextBlob(
        string text,
        SKFont font,
        SKPaint paint)
    {
        var key = new TextCacheKey(
            text,
            font.Typeface.FamilyName,
            font.Size,
            font.Typeface.FontWeight,
            font.Typeface.FontSlant
        );

        if (_cache.TryGetValue(key, out var cached))
        {
            return cached;
        }

        // Perform expensive text shaping
        var blob = SKTextBlob.Create(text, font);

        // Evict old entries if cache is full
        if (_cache.Count >= MaxCacheSize)
        {
            var oldest = _cache.Keys.First();
            _cache[oldest].Dispose();
            _cache.Remove(oldest);
        }

        _cache[key] = blob;
        return blob;
    }

    public void Clear()
    {
        foreach (var blob in _cache.Values)
        {
            blob.Dispose();
        }
        _cache.Clear();
    }
}
```

Integrate this into `SkiaLabel`:

```csharp
public class OptimizedSkiaLabel : SkiaLabel
{
    private static readonly TextRenderCache _textCache = new();

    protected override void DrawText(SKCanvas canvas, SKPaint paint)
    {
        using var font = paint.ToFont();
        var textBlob = _textCache.GetOrCreateTextBlob(Text, font, paint);

        canvas.DrawText(textBlob, (float)X, (float)Y, paint);
